Option 1: 

Using extra space: 
1. We will create an array of double size and populate array with same elements
 arr = {1,2,3}
 so, arr = {1,2,3,1,2,3}
 Now apply kaden's alogorithm in this new arr and return answer;
 
 Option 2: 
 
 1. In a single loop
 2. Invert the array element
 3. maintain sum of whole array after inverting element.
 4. applying kaden's algorithm to invert element and get the max value.
 5. meanwhile in same loop check if all elements are negative, if yes then return min value
 6. else, if all elements are not negative
 7. then now we have inverted array sum and max element 
 so answer would be : -(array sum - max)
 
 
